<user>106292633542509597757</user><username>Shaffy Nasser<//username><time>1600905382532< /time><Rating>5</Rating>< Review>
The best tasting Chinese food in the Antelope Valley for sure.
A great balance of Chinese sauces and flavors. They have a large choice in the menu. Some of the best dishes for me are Kung Pao 3 flavor, diced beef and of course their Dragon house fried rice.
I am sure everyone will enjoy their cuisine.<//Review>

< Review>
Don Wilkes is a great guy with a great shop. After some bad experiences with Stockton Dodge and Sonora dodges service departments I am leery about taking any of my vehicles to a shop. But my wife's car is still under warranty so it has to go to an approved mechanic. Don diagnosed our car and found out it has a faulty PCM (powertrain control module) it is a dealer only part so the warranty wouldn't cover any of Don's work or the rental car. We offered to pay for the rental but he refused to let us.  He ate the total cost of everything and referred us to Folsom Dodge said it was a quick lesson on doing warranty work and fine print. He will have my business whenever I need a shop and it's not dealer only parts. Again, thanks Don.< /Review>

<Review>Generally, I am a fan of Rubio's having been to several locations.

My SO and I visited this location on Feb 15th.  The experience was far less than satisfactory.  We stood in line behind three people and in front of two others while another couple was trying to order.

Part way through their order process, the Cashier stopped and busied himself with other tasks, delivering plates to seated customers, answering the phone, and speaking to patrons about problems.  Finally, the order taker completed the order process with this couple, and then disappeared from the register while we 7 customers waited in line.

It took 12-15 minutes before we were able to complete our order. Including the cashier taking time out multiple times in the process for other tasks.

The fruit type drinks were completely missing.  Even the tanks on top of the respective coolers were missing.

The salsa bar was a mess.  Some of the salsas were low and seemed to be there for some time.  The verde salsa was very thin and watery.  The jalapeno bowl had only about 8 slices of pepper left and no carrots or onions.

There were no silverware in the container.  When I asked at the counter, he pointed at some plastic ware.  The forks therein were among the cheapest, most flimsy stuff I have ever seen.  Nowhere near so nice as what can be purchased in bulk at Costco.

After we ordered, about 6:45, a fellow walked in from outside and into the kitchen and put on an apron.  Apparently just off a break, I wondered about the work schedules that would have a worker off at about 6:30 on a Saturday evening.

The food was okay.  As we were finishing, there seemed to be some sort of disagreement in the kitchen.  Their voices were obvious throughout the restaurant.

This location must be an embarrassment to the franchise.  I attribute most of these experiences to extremely poor training and management.  I am expecting that perhaps this store is on its way out.  The franchise owner has cut corners and is probably unwilling to spend the money to make this business successful.

I will not go back here.</Review></record>

<rating>1</rating><response>{'time': 1561766142433, 'text': 'Thank you for your feedback.\nIn the United States, it is very common for high-rise buildings to be managed by a separate company, which takes care of all the air conditioning and cleaning services in the entire building. In the case of LSI, the air condition and cleaning services are both controlled by the building management, not by LSI. LSI has repeatedly made the building management aware of these issues, and we have taken steps within our power to improve the situation.\n\nFirst, in order to make the classes more comfortable in the evening when the building management shuts off the central air conditioning, LSI has brought in individual air conditioning units.\n\nSecond, LSI has repeatedly spoken to building management about the quality of the cleaning services and has documented cases where the cleaning services have failed. Additionally, students\' personal hygiene may affect the cleanliness of certain areas of the school (such as leaving undergarments in the bathroom). In these cases, we need to investigate who is doing this and talk to them in private about being more considerate of others.\n\nFinally,  as an accredited school, we are required to have a clear curriculum with textbooks and syllabi for all of our classes. This means that students need to have an actual textbook to study English when taking classes at accredited, legitimate schools in California. It recently came to our attention that many of our evening students did not have textbooks despite having been in class for more than a week.  This was surprising since the most basic requirement at ANY school is for students to have their books.  Our LSI teachers have always been excellent and understanding of student needs, but even the best teacher in the world would have a hard time teaching any class where students had no material to work out of. This could be why certain teachers may choose to leave a school because some students refuse to buy materials for the class and still expect the teachers to carry on with the class without any material. LSI has done everything it possibly can to keep costs low and affordable for our students while still providing an excellent educational program.  As such, many of our own LSI books are available in FREE eBook format and in some classes, free class copies are offered to the point where students need only buy 1 or 2 books for the entire term!  Therefore, your assertion that we "ruin" your visa if you don\'t buy a book is simply not true. We only ask that you meet the basic requirements of international students studying in the United States.\n\nWe hope that you now understand how the system works in the United States for the management of buildings in an urban area and for international students studying English in the United States.'}<//response>< user_name>

<rating>2</rating>< Text>
I love cheese. I love simple things. I always liked this stall when I walked in the Ferry Building.
So how could this place go wrong?

I don't mind paying $10 for a sandwich if it's quality and filled with ingredients.. but that wasn't the case here. I mean, they did use quality bread and cheese. The thing is, there was BARELY ANY CHEESE.
There was only like A LAYER of cheese and maybe like one slice of meat.... I expected more for a place that specializes in cheese. No ooey gooey magic factor when you think of a grilled cheese sandwich..

No.<//Text>

I saw a woman walking through the Ferry Building with a plate of cheesy yum and I demanded she tell me where it came from. She complied and pointed me in the direction of Cowgirl Creamery. We began to walk through the store, and then spotted "the Sidekick" next door.

A man with a really big ball of cheese and a large unit for heating it stood out front of Sidekick. It was kind of unclear how to obtain a plate, but I eventually figured out there were two places to order and pay, one on either side of the man. It was a short wait for the food after we ordered. My husband and I each had the melted asiago cheese on bread. ("Weekend Raclette - $5.95)

The cheese was wonderful, the bread was kind of soggy. It was really messy and hard to eat, but it was good. A few pickled veggies were served on the side.

< rating>
4</rating>
< review>
The sidekick is a mini storefront that deals mainly in milk based beverages and some serious grilled cheese sandwiches. The beverages are quite tasty, and I tried a few of them, which included the raspberry spritzer thing, a cafe au lait, and one of the chocolate based bevs. All of them were fantastic. The sandwiches were good, buttered grilled bread with fantastic cheese and some meat inside. More of a quality over quantity when it comes to the filling, I had no complaints wolfing them down as the denizens of the Ferry Building's shopping habit swarmed around us.
The staff was just super friendly, which isn't uncommon in San Francisco, but it was absolutely pleasant having them be a part of my experience here.<//review>

< user_id>
108522825854726077468</user_id>
< review>
The cheese grits with a poached egg and pancetta might not be to everyone's tastes (as a Canuck, it's not something I see very often) but it grew on me. I think they use a sharp cheddar, which gives the grits good flavour, and the egg was poached perfectly.

I've also enjoyed their burrata salad at lunch; there's a healthy dose of burrata, which plays well with the salad's asparagus and green beans. Whether you're grabbing something en route to a ferry, or want to people watch in the busy corridors of the Ferry Building, this is a good place to do so.<//review>

< username>
Jerome Fried (Ironman)<//username>
< date>
1368827772545</date>
< rating>
5<//rating>
< text>
The cafe-style extension of local Cowgirl Creamery, known as Sidekick Cafe & Milk Bar, is situated prominently on the corner adjacent to the Creamery's Ferry Building cheese shop, in the center of the promenade, and serves fresh milk, several varieties of cheeses  to suit anyone's tastes, and all manner of other dairy-based treats.  The grilled cheese with pancetta is strongly suggested, offering all of the intense saltiness of Italian bacon paired with the creaminess that comes with a locally-sourced, fresh cheese of your selection, grilled and melted to perfection.

Other dairy products include a rich, creamy, decadent chocolate mousse and an Earl Grey Tea panna cotta that any desert-lover would enjoy.  If you want fresh, wholesome, locally-sourced ingredients, prepared with comfort food in mind, you've found another great place in San Francisco...<//text>

<resp>None</resp><rating>4<//rating><Text>Sure, there are probably a lot of options in San Francisco if you want a grilled cheese, but not many of them are as memorable as the Sidekick Cafe & Milk Bar. Located in the Ferry Building and next door to Cowgirl Creamery, the sandwich artisans whip up some pretty delectable dairy products for the famished passerby. Our group munched on the grilled cheese special of the day with goat gouda (um, yes!), gruyere and fromage blanc. I tried it with and without Pancetta and both were gooey with crisp bread and a sweet and spicy relish of some kind that really made the sandwich. My chai milk tea wasn't huge on the flavor, but the friendly service was a huge win. We ended our dairy feast with some chocolate panna cotta. Holy goodness was that little snack a good one! Rich and thick with a smooth and creamy texture, don't miss this little hidden treat on your next visit.< /Text><gmap_id>0x8085805f18233a79:0xe9aff9d78dd5bb13< /gmap_id>< user_name>

< review>
For a small town its definitely evident it fits in perfectly, small town mall. We DO have a Macy's and some newer franchises have bought vacant spaces and I think the mall is really doing the best it can. Rent was raised at Town Center Mall, so there's QUITE a bit of other big name companies & shopping centers where you can feel like you've been shopping at a nicer mall. With the exception of a few stores,  I'd have never felt a desire to go here...but there is construction of housing  establishments AS WELL as shopping centers. We are not SUCH an invisible SMALL town anymore. Over 500k+ individuals living in the vicinity so retailers stepped up their efforts to grow as our town turns into a city. .....There's talk we could be getting a Victoria's Secret. The x-ray and scanning was done in a timely and comfortable manner for my son.  Post scanning doctor explained the problem statement and examination summary very clearly using models and also showed us how her Invisalign treatment plan will completely eliminate the crowding of teeth for my son in addition to expanding his jaw arches to satisfactory level.  In the past, we were discouraged due to "uncomfortable" treatment options like expanders etc. that we were not ready for.  Dr. Alexa Alborzi explained with confidence how she can handle Phase 1 and Phase2  with her vast experience and expertise and also showed some before and after experience pictures to boost our confidence.  In fact our primary dentist also raised some doubt and concern about our decision to move forward with Dr. Alborzi as many dental professionals have limited experience on new technology and advances and even out of their utmost care for their patients they end up overlooking modern options available for treating orthodontic conditions. <name>Kristina Martin</name><Time>1560792515999< /Time><rate>1< /rate>< Review>
My son and I both rec'd treatment beginning in 2012-2013 and have been in retainers for several years now. My son had traditional braces and his experience was unremarkable (hence one star). My experience was totally different. I did Invisalign, which ultimately worked but took a year longer than quoted (with Dr. Alborzi showing up as condescending and argumentative during the many complications from treatment through retention). But I'm not even writing about that, I'm writing about the predatory practice that I just experienced this morning when I went in to replace the retainer I lost on Friday. Retainers are pretty important...without them, you lose all the time and money that came before. And retainers aren't forever: the materials break, they can get misplaced. While I was still an "active" patient (as of 2018?!) I paid $300 for retainers. This morning they were going to charge me $600 per, $1,200 for two retainers (I wanted a spare on-hand). When I said it was too much, they gave me one other option of getting four for $960. This is an exploitative, predatory practice. The true character of a provider reveals when you've already paid the largest bill.<//Review>

< Text>
Of all the clothing subscription boxes, Trunk Club seemed the most safe since it is a Nordstrom company, known for exceptional customer service.

Unfortunately, Trunk Club falls severely short.

Pros:
The clothes are fairly priced - the same as what can be found on Nordstrom's website.
The process is very easy. Everything comes in a box with 5 days to review. Ship back returns in the same box with a prepaid label and closure adhesive.

Cons:
In a months time, the stylist assigned to the account changed 3x. Not sure if this was due to turnover.
Nordstrom's flexible return policy does not extend to Trunk Club, even though the same clothes are being sold on both Nordstrom and Trunk Club.

This review applies to the online service.</Text>

<rating>5<//rating>< Text>
After waiting a year to finally try trunk club, I was pleasantly surprised they had a club House less than 5 miles from home. I set up an appointment and was paired with Annie. Upon arriving, my girlfriend and I were offered drinks and a seat by Paul. As soon as Annie walked in the door, my gf said "I like her style, I bet that must be Annie! " sure enough, it was!

Annie came and introduced herself, listened to everything I had to say about the style I was aiming for and how I needed her expert guidance, then she went off, only to return with many outfits that all seemed perfect! If something didn't fit right, she immediately went off in search of something better. 2.5 hours later, I left the store feeling like a new man.

The entire experience was fun, the staff is great, and the clothes are perfect!!! Thank you Annie and team Trunk Club!

Update:

While Annie is no longer with the company, I still do a lot of shopping here. Jessica is my new go-to stylist, can't recommend her enough!</Text>

<pics>None<//pics><rate>5</rate>< review>
We would like to recognize the wonderful service experience we had with Alex from Metro Towing.

We got a flat tire on the I580-W highway near Tracy on a long return trip from LA. We used Geico Emergency Road Service who assigned Metro Towing as our service provider to help us through this. Geico gave us a 30 minute time-frame for the towing service to reach us.

We were apprehensive about a long wait in the high afternoon heat but we were pleasantly surprised to see the flashing lights of Alex's two truck in our rearview mirror within 15 minutes.

Alex worked with us on replacing our spare tire which looked fine at first. We soon found out that it was under inflated once the car was lowered from the jack. Alex immedietly helped us by towing us to the nearest gas station and filling up our spare tire.

We are grateful to Alex and Metro Towing for going the extra mile to get us happily on our way home after a long journey. My children were ecstatic to have one last ride on top of a tow truck.

Alex is kind, courteous and professional. He is a great asset to Metro Towing's service family.<//review>
